---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About | Imagination Grove Academy" description="A new kind of childcare across Indiana &amp; Kentucky, built by local educators. Read our philosophy, meet the team, and see our licensing and credentials.">

    <!-- ========== HERO ========== -->
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="fade-in">
          <p class="eyebrow">About IGA</p>
          <h1>A new kind of childcare, built by local educators.</h1>
          <p>Imagination Grove Academy is a new kind of childcare, built by local educators across Indiana and Kentucky. We are not a franchise. We are real, licensed schools designed around what early childhood actually needs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== OUR STORY ========== -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="story-grid fade-in">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Our story</p>
            <h2>The story behind IGA.</h2>
            <div class="content-placeholder">
              <p class="content-placeholder-label">Section needs alignment with client</p>
              <p class="content-placeholder-hint">Story framing TBD. The client (a real estate development company investing in IGA) will determine whether this section emphasizes the school's mission, the developer's commitment to the community, or some combination. Hold off on copy until that conversation happens.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="placeholder-img" role="img" aria-label="Photo placeholder">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
              <rect x="8" y="12" width="32" height="24" rx="2" fill="#6CB43A" opacity="0.4"/>
              <circle cx="18" cy="22" r="3" fill="#1F5247" opacity="0.6"/>
              <path d="M8 36l8-10 6 6 10-12 8 12" stroke="#1F5247" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
            </svg>
            <span class="placeholder-label">Photo: building exterior or classroom interior, TBD with client</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== LEADERSHIP & TEAM (TBD WITH CLIENT) ========== -->
    <section class="section section-green-bg">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <p class="eyebrow">Leadership &amp; team</p>
          <h2>Who is behind IGA.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="content-placeholder content-placeholder--wide fade-in">
          <p class="content-placeholder-label">Section needs alignment with client</p>
          <p class="content-placeholder-hint">Leadership framing TBD. Options to discuss with the client: (1) feature the development company that is building IGA, (2) introduce the operating leadership (Tyler and a hired director), (3) keep this minimal and let the teaching team carry the page once hired. Whichever direction we choose, the visual pattern can be a 2-up or 3-up card grid in this slot. Hold off on copy and headshots until that conversation happens.</p>
        </div>

        <aside class="hiring-note fade-in">
          <p><strong>About our teaching team:</strong> Every IGA teacher will be degree-qualified, background-checked, and trained specifically in the age range they teach. The team is <span class="placeholder-inline">[hiring now]</span> for the Fall 2026 opening. Bios and headshots will be published as each teacher signs on. <a href="/enroll" class="text-link">Schedule a tour &rarr;</a> to meet whoever has joined the team by then.</p>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== PHILOSOPHY ========== -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <p class="eyebrow">Our philosophy</p>
          <h2>Kids build 90% of their brain architecture by age 5.</h2>
          <p>Language. Emotional regulation. Curiosity. Self-image. The adults in that window aren't just keeping a child safe. They are wiring the human that child becomes. That is a lot of pressure, and a lot of opportunity.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="philosophy-intro fade-in">We do not subscribe to a single brand-name philosophy because we think each one gets part of early childhood right and part of it wrong. Instead, we combine play-based learning, teacher-guided structure, daily nature time, and relationships over programs.</p>

        <div class="philosophy-cols fade-in">
          <div class="phil-col dont">
            <h3>What we don't do</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Screens for under-3s. Limited educational video for 4-5s, rarely.</li>
              <li>Worksheets, flashcards, or rote drills.</li>
              <li>Rushing the developmental timeline.</li>
              <li>Shame-based discipline. Ever.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="phil-col do">
            <h3>What we do instead</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Narrate emotions: "I can see you're frustrated. It's hard when..."</li>
              <li>Offer choices: "Would you like the red cup or the blue cup?"</li>
              <li>Respect the child's pace.</li>
              <li>Teach conflict resolution explicitly.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== LICENSING & CREDENTIALS ========== -->
    <section class="section section-teal-bg" id="safety">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header fade-in">
          <p class="eyebrow">Licensing &amp; credentials</p>
          <h2>The details that actually matter.</h2>
          <p>Here is the paperwork you won't see on most childcare websites, because we think you deserve to see it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="credentials-block fade-in">

          <h3>Our licensing</h3>
          <p class="credentials-note">Each IGA campus is independently state-licensed. Our Indiana locations (Bargersville, Fishers, New Palestine) are licensed by the Indiana FSSA. Our Lexington, KY location is licensed by the Kentucky Division of Child Care. See each <a href="/locations" class="text-link">location page</a> for capacity, licensing body, and other details. License numbers are available upon request.</p>
          <dl class="credentials-list">
            <div>
              <dt>License type</dt>
              <dd>State-licensed childcare centers (Indiana &amp; Kentucky)</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>License number</dt>
              <dd>Available upon request</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Licensed capacity</dt>
              <dd>Varies by location &mdash; see each location page</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>State inspection record</dt>
              <dd>Available upon request at each campus</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Health department inspection</dt>
              <dd>Conducted at each location per state schedule</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>

          <h3>Staff credentials</h3>
          <dl class="credentials-list">
            <div>
              <dt>Lead teachers</dt>
              <dd>Minimum Associate's degree in Early Childhood Education or related field</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Background checks</dt>
              <dd>100% of staff: FBI, state criminal history, sex offender registry, DCS</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>CPR &amp; first aid</dt>
              <dd>100% of staff CPR and pediatric first-aid certified</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Annual training</dt>
              <dd>Hours exceed state-mandated minimums</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>

          <h3>Insurance</h3>
          <p class="credentials-note">General liability, workers' compensation, and specialized child care liability coverage are all current.</p>

          <p class="credentials-footnote">Full health and safety policies, including cleaning schedules, illness procedures, emergency protocols, and medication administration standards, will live on the Resources page once published.</p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ========== CTA BAND ========== -->
    <section class="cta-band section-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="fade-in">
          <h2>The fastest way to know if IGA is right.</h2>
          <p>Read this far and still not sure? That's normal. Tour the building, meet a teacher, and decide for yourself.</p>
          <a href="/enroll" class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Schedule a Free Tour</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

</BaseLayout>
